{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T15:59:12.933Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What It Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Property-Based Testing (PBT)"},{"type":"text","text":" is a testing approach where tests validate "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"properties"},{"type":"text","text":" (invariants or rules) that must hold true across a wide range of inputs, rather than asserting specific input→output pairs. Instead of saying \"If I input 3, I expect 9,\" you say \"For any integer input, squaring it should always produce a non-negative result\"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The testing framework "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"automatically generates hundreds to thousands of random inputs"},{"type":"text","text":" and checks if these properties hold for every input-output pair. PBT is also known as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"generative testing\""},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"QuickCheck testing\""},{"type":"text","text":" (named after the Haskell library that popularized it)."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why It Matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without property-based testing:\n- Edge cases slip through (null, empty, maximum values, negative numbers)\n- Complex algorithms have hidden bugs you didn't think to test\n- You can't test millions of possible inputs manually\n- Example-based tests miss invalid scenarios\n- Code changes introduce subtle bugs in boundary conditions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Property-based testing "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"discovers bugs automatically"},{"type":"text","text":" by generating test data you wouldn't consider, finding issues in complex algorithms before they reach production."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefits"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefit"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Impact"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Covers edge cases"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Finds bugs you didn't think to test manually"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Generates many inputs"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Tests 100–1000x more scenarios than manual tests"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Minimal test code"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"One property test replaces many unit tests"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Discovers hidden bugs"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Finds issues in complex algorithms, sorting, transformations"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reusable test data"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Generators work across multiple tests"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fails on discovery"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Automatically finds specific input that breaks property"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Suitable for fuzzing"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Extends to security testing (memory errors, crashes)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Trade-offs"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Limitation"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Consequence"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Slower execution"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can be slower due to 1000s of random inputs"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Complex to define properties"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hard to articulate what \"should always be true\""}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Not for all scenarios"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Bad for UI, simple business logic, specific cases"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"False positives"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Random inputs may include invalid data"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Less readable"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Tests don't show specific examples clearly"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Debugging difficulty"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When property fails, need to understand why for that input"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How It Works"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Core Concept: Invariants"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"invariant"},{"type":"text","text":" is a condition that should "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"always hold true"},{"type":"text","text":" regardless of input. Think of it as a \"universal truth\" about your code."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Property-based test checks output differently"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Unit test"},{"type":"text","text":": Checks output is identical to pre-computed expected result\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Property test"},{"type":"text","text":": Checks properties that should be true for every input-output pair"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Testing Process"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Define property"},{"type":"text","text":" (invariant) the software must satisfy"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Framework generates"},{"type":"text","text":" 100–1000+ random inputs"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Run program"},{"type":"text","text":" on all inputs"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Assert property holds"},{"type":"text","text":" for each input-output pair"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"If fails"},{"type":"text","text":", framework shows the specific input that broke it"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Property-Based Test Structure"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Property-based test template\n@given(<input_type>)  # Define input type\ndef test_property(input):\n    result = your_function(input)\n    assert property_holds(result, input)  # General truth, not specific value"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"When to Use It"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scenario"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Property-Based Testing"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mathematical functions"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ Yes - invariants like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"a + b = b + a"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sorting/algorithms"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ Yes - stability, correctness, monotonicity"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Data transformations"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ Yes - round-trip properties (serialize→deserialize)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"String operations"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ Yes - reverse, concatenate, case conversions"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Complex algorithms"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ Yes - graph traversal, search, compression"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Simple business logic"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"❌ No - example-based tests are clearer"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"UI interactions"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"❌ No - too complex to define properties"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Specific input cases"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"❌ No - use unit tests for known examples"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When NOT to use"},{"type":"text","text":": Don't use PBT for simple business logic, specific cases with known expected outputs, or UI testing—example-based (unit) tests are better there."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How to Implement"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example: Property-Based Testing with Hypothesis (Python)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"from hypothesis import given, integers, lists\n\n# Property 1: Adding zero doesn't change value\n@given(integers())\ndef test_add_zero(x):\n    assert x + 0 == x\n\n# Property 2: Multiplication is commutative\n@given(integers(), integers())\ndef test_multiplication_commutative(a, b):\n    assert a * b == b * a\n\n# Property 3: Sorting is stable (sorted once = sorted twice)\n@given(lists(integers()))\ndef test_sort_stability(items):\n    sorted_once = sorted(items)\n    sorted_twice = sorted(sorted_once)\n    assert sorted_once == sorted_twice\n\n# Property 4: Sorted list is monotonic (each element <= next)\n@given(lists(integers()))\ndef test_sorted_monotonic(items):\n    sorted_list = sorted(items)\n    for i in range(len(sorted_list) - 1):\n        assert sorted_list[i] <= sorted_list[i + 1]\n\n# Property 5: Reverse twice = original\n@given(lists(integers()))\ndef test_reverse_stability(items):\n    reversed_once = items[::-1]\n    reversed_twice = reversed_once[::-1]\n    assert reversed_twice == items\n\n# Run with pytest\n# pytest test_properties.py"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example: Serialization Round-Trip Property"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"from hypothesis import given, text\n\n# Property: Serialization round-trip\n# Every output from serialization should be accepted by deserialization\n@given(text())\ndef test_serialize_deserialize_roundtrip(original_text):\n    # Serialize\n    serialized = json.dumps(original_text)\n    \n    # Deserialize\n    deserialized = json.loads(serialized)\n    \n    # Property: Original equals deserialized\n    assert original_text == deserialized"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example: Property-Based Testing with jqwik (Java)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"java"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import jqwik.api.API;\n\npublic class SortingProperties {\n    \n    @API\n    void sortStability(@ForAll List<Integer> items) {\n        List<Integer> sortedOnce = sort(items);\n        List<Integer> sortedTwice = sort(sortedOnce);\n        \n        // Property: Sorting is stable\n        Assertions.assertEquals(sortedOnce, sortedTwice);\n    }\n    \n    @API\n    void sortMonotonicity(@ForAll List<Integer> items) {\n        List<Integer> sorted = sort(items);\n        \n        // Property: Sorted list is monotonic\n        for (int i = 0; i < sorted.size() - 1; i++) {\n            Assertions.assertTrue(sorted.get(i) <= sorted.get(i + 1));\n        }\n    }\n}"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example: Property-Based Testing with fast-check (JavaScript)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"javascript"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { fc, test } from '@fast-check/jest';\n\n// Property: Reversing array twice gives original\ntest('array reverse is stable', () => {\n  fc.assert(\n    fc.property(fc.array(fc.integer()), (arr) => {\n      const reversedOnce = arr.reverse();\n      const reversedTwice = reversedOnce.reverse();\n      \n      // Property: Original equals double-reversed\n      expect(reversedTwice).toEqual(arr);\n    })\n  );\n});\n\n// Property: Array length unchanged after reverse\ntest('array length preserved after reverse', () => {\n  fc.assert(\n    fc.property(fc.array(fc.integer()), (arr) => {\n      const originalLength = arr.length;\n      arr.reverse();\n      \n      // Property: Length unchanged\n      expect(arr.length).toBe(originalLength);\n    })\n  );\n});"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Property Types"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Property Type"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Description"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Invariants"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Always true regardless of input"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"x + 0 = x"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Symmetry"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Order doesn't matter"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"a + b = b + a"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Idempotence"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Repeated application same as single"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"sort(sort(x)) = sort(x)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Round-trip"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Transform → reverse = original"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"serialize(deserialize(x)) = x"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Monotonicity"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ordered relationship maintained"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"sorted[i] ≤ sorted[i+1]"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Conservation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Some aspect preserved"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"reverse(arr).length = arr.length"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Property-Based Testing vs Unit Testing"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Unit Testing (Example-Based)"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Property-Based Testing"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Input generation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Predefined, manual inputs"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Random, auto-generated"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Focus"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Specific input→output scenarios"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Properties true for any input"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Speed"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fast (few tests)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"col