 Takeaways"},{"type":"text","text":":\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Property-based testing"},{"type":"text","text":" defines "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"invariants"},{"type":"text","text":" (rules that must always hold) and auto-generates 100–1000+ random inputs to verify them\n2. Instead of \"input 3 → expect 9,\" say \"for any integer, squaring produces non-negative result\"\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best for"},{"type":"text","text":": mathematical functions, sorting/algorithms, data transformations, string operations\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Not for"},{"type":"text","text":": simple business logic, UI interactions, specific cases with known outputs\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Complements unit tests"},{"type":"text","text":" — finds edge cases unit tests miss, doesn't replace them\n6. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Shrinking"},{"type":"text","text":" finds minimal failing input for easier debugging\n7. Popular frameworks: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Hypothesis"},{"type":"text","text":" (Python), "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"fast-check"},{"type":"text","text":" (JavaScript), "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"jqwik"},{"type":"text","text":" (Java), "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"QuickCheck"},{"type":"text","text":" (Haskell)"}]}]}}
